        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 10 at 5:30PM EDT by NWS Raleigh NC</headline>
        <description>At 530 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Badin Lake, moving southeast at 10 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Troy, Badin Lake, Biscoe, Badin, Mount Gilead, Star, Candor, Uwharrie
Haven, Steeds, and Eldorado.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
